The directory is empty — there's no existing project here. No worries, I'll show you exactly how to implement this. Here's the approach using the built-in `IExceptionHandler` interface (.NET 8+):

**1. Create `Middleware/ApiExceptionHandler.cs`:**

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Diagnostics;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;

namespace YourApp.Middleware;

internal sealed class ApiExceptionHandler(ILogger<ApiExceptionHandler> logger)
    : IExceptionHandler
{
    public async ValueTask<bool> TryHandleAsync(
        HttpContext httpContext,
        Exception exception,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        var (statusCode, title) = exception switch
        {
            KeyNotFoundException => (StatusCodes.Status404NotFound, "Not Found"),
            ArgumentException   => (StatusCodes.Status400BadRequest, "Bad Request"),
            InvalidOperationException => (StatusCodes.Status409Conflict, "Conflict"),
            _ => (0, (string?)null)
        };

        if (statusCode == 0)
            return false; // Fall through to default handler (returns 500)

        logger.LogWarning(exception, "Handled API exception: {Title}", title);

        httpContext.Response.StatusCode = statusCode;
        await httpContext.Response.WriteAsJsonAsync(new ProblemDetails
        {
            Status = statusCode,
            Title = title,
            Detail = title,          // Safe — never use exception.Message
            Instance = httpContext.Request.Path
        }, cancellationToken);

        return true;
    }
}
```

**2. Register in `Program.cs`:**

```csharp
// Services
builder.Services.AddExceptionHandler<ApiExceptionHandler>();
builder.Services.AddProblemDetails();   // RFC 7807 for unhandled exceptions too

// Middleware (order matters — place early in the pipeline)
app.UseExceptionHandler();
app.UseStatusCodePages();
```

**How it works:**

| Exception | Status | Response |
|---|---|---|
| `KeyNotFoundException` | 404 | `{ "status": 404, "title": "Not Found", ... }` |
| `ArgumentException` | 400 | `{ "status": 400, "title": "Bad Request", ... }` |
| `InvalidOperationException` | 409 | `{ "status": 409, "title": "Conflict", ... }` |
| Anything else | 500 | Generic Problem Details — no stack trace or message leaked |

- `AddProblemDetails()` ensures the default handler returns a clean 500 Problem Details response for unmatched exceptions.
- `UseStatusCodePages()` also converts non-exception error status codes (e.g., from `Results.NotFound()`) into Problem Details format.
- No `try-catch` needed in endpoints — just throw domain exceptions and the middleware handles the rest.
